WEBVTT

00:05.171 --> 00:12.303
* Beyond the yellow
brick roooad *

00:12.345 --> 00:14.514
John: Four chairs!

00:14.556 --> 00:16.933
A good friend of mine
who's no longer here,

00:16.975 --> 00:18.268
he taught me
a little trick.

00:19.936 --> 00:21.479
Gwen: Oh!

00:21.521 --> 00:25.734
The spirit of Blake Shelton
came into the room saying,

00:25.775 --> 00:26.985
"Pick Niall."

00:27.027 --> 00:28.445
And I was like,
"This might work."

00:28.486 --> 00:29.946
You want to sing
a song together?

00:29.988 --> 00:31.197
That would be fun.
Yeah.

00:31.239 --> 00:32.407
Niall: Coming into this,

00:32.449 --> 00:34.200
I thought John Legend
was a gentleman.

00:34.242 --> 00:35.285
How wrong was I?

00:35.326 --> 00:40.999
* I give you all of me *

00:41.041 --> 00:42.208
Get away, get away.
[ Laughter ]

00:42.250 --> 00:43.710
He's playing dirty right now.

00:43.752 --> 00:45.879
If this doesn't work,
I've lost all my mojo.

00:45.920 --> 00:49.257
This has been quite entertaining
for all of us.

00:49.299 --> 00:52.510
So, Mara, who do you pick
as your coach?

00:52.552 --> 00:54.054
Whoa!

00:54.095 --> 00:56.598
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:56.639 --> 00:59.768
Come on!
Don't break my heart, Mara!

00:59.809 --> 01:02.604
**

01:02.645 --> 01:03.897
Oh, that'll do it.

01:03.938 --> 01:04.898
Come on!

01:04.939 --> 01:06.024
Who should I go with?

01:06.066 --> 01:08.443
**

01:08.485 --> 01:09.736
I'm gonna go with John.

01:09.778 --> 01:12.072
Yes!
* Oh, these are the days *

01:12.113 --> 01:13.948
* These are the days *

01:13.990 --> 01:15.575
That duet was so good.

01:15.617 --> 01:17.118
Man!

01:17.160 --> 01:18.244
Yeah!

01:18.286 --> 01:21.915
I had to get Mara on my team.

01:21.956 --> 01:23.583
I'm so happy!
[ Laughs ]

01:23.625 --> 01:25.085
We didn't have
a chance.

01:25.126 --> 01:26.628
She's soulful.

01:26.670 --> 01:30.090
She's got amazing tone,
amazing power in her voice.

01:30.131 --> 01:31.591
Take that, Niall.

01:32.467 --> 01:34.552
No.
[ Laughter ]

01:34.594 --> 01:37.430
Mara: My first pick
was initially Reba.

01:37.472 --> 01:41.184
But after singing
that song with John...
Okay. What?!

01:41.226 --> 01:42.435
...I was like, "This is it."

01:42.477 --> 01:44.270
Thank you.
[ Chuckles ]

01:44.312 --> 01:45.814
My mind is blown.

01:45.855 --> 01:48.942
I'm actually disgusted
by both of your guys' behavior.

01:48.983 --> 01:50.777
Why?
That was embarrassing.

01:50.819 --> 01:51.778
Yeah.

01:51.820 --> 01:53.029
Reba: It was shameless.

01:53.071 --> 01:54.614
But, man, I better step up
to the plate here.

01:54.656 --> 01:56.282
Why did he have
to do that?

01:56.324 --> 01:58.284
Any time you can
block someone, block John.

01:58.326 --> 01:59.828
That's the last time
I speak to him.

01:59.869 --> 02:01.413
[ Laughter ]

02:01.454 --> 02:04.040
Blake, this is your fault.
You cursed the foam finger.

02:04.082 --> 02:05.291
**

02:05.333 --> 02:07.168
Get out of here, Shelton.

02:07.210 --> 02:08.962
Welcome to Foley, Missouri.

02:09.004 --> 02:12.382
This is our only stoplight
in our very small town,

02:12.424 --> 02:14.718
so get a good look at it.

02:14.759 --> 02:16.011
I'm Ruby Leigh.

02:16.052 --> 02:19.139
I am 16, and I am from
a small town of 68 people

02:19.180 --> 02:20.557
called Foley, Missouri.

02:20.598 --> 02:23.143
There's not really anything
in my town.

02:23.184 --> 02:24.644
Like, we don't even have
a gas station

02:24.686 --> 02:26.312
[chuckles]
or a fire department

02:26.354 --> 02:27.772
or a police department
or a school.

02:27.814 --> 02:29.482
**

02:29.524 --> 02:32.485
It's just us, couple
of corn cobs here in Foley.

02:32.527 --> 02:34.487
So, one of the activities
that we love to do

02:34.529 --> 02:35.989
is redneck sledding.

02:36.031 --> 02:37.532
* Whoa-oa-oa *

02:37.574 --> 02:40.785
Redneck sledding, you get
the top of a car hood,

02:40.827 --> 02:41.828
you flip it over,

02:41.870 --> 02:43.371
you attach it
to the back of a truck.

02:43.413 --> 02:44.998
Hang on.
You guys, hang on.

02:45.040 --> 02:46.666
You just go around.

02:46.708 --> 02:48.501
Whoo!

02:48.543 --> 02:50.628
You just fling yourself
until you fall off.

02:50.670 --> 02:53.423
Ruby actually broke
her collarbone doing that.

02:53.465 --> 02:55.467
[ Screaming]

02:55.508 --> 02:57.344
Yeah, they rolled over me
by accident.

02:57.385 --> 02:59.346
So [laughs]
Yeah.

02:59.387 --> 03:01.264
Man: 45 out, 45 seconds.

03:01.306 --> 03:03.016
I'm from such a small town,

03:03.058 --> 03:04.392
there's not a lot
of opportunities.

03:04.434 --> 03:05.852
There's 68 people.

03:05.894 --> 03:09.397
So, it's like my whole town
is here, plus more.

03:09.439 --> 03:11.232
I do want to make
my town proud.

03:11.274 --> 03:12.609
If someone were to turn for me,

03:12.650 --> 03:15.153
it would totally change
my life forever.

03:15.195 --> 03:17.489
I was extremely excited

03:17.530 --> 03:19.783
to find out that Reba
was on "The Voice."

03:19.824 --> 03:21.659
Also, I'd love to work
with Gwen

03:21.701 --> 03:24.662
because she's won
with a younger artist before.

03:25.413 --> 03:27.832
This is the biggest thing
I've ever done.

03:27.874 --> 03:30.877
**

03:30.919 --> 03:32.295
Oh!

03:32.337 --> 03:34.339
**

03:34.381 --> 03:37.717
* I wanna be
a cowboy's sweetheart *

03:37.759 --> 03:41.054
* Wanna learn
to rope and ride *

03:41.096 --> 03:44.599
* Wanna ride o'er the plains
and the desert *

03:44.641 --> 03:47.894
* Out west of the great divide *

03:47.936 --> 03:51.398
* I wanna hear
the coyotes howling *

03:51.439 --> 03:54.693
* While the sun sets
in the west *

03:54.734 --> 03:58.697
* I wanna be
a cowboy's sweetheart *

03:58.738 --> 04:01.950
* The life I love the best *

04:01.991 --> 04:04.244
[ Yodeling ]

04:04.285 --> 04:11.001
**

04:11.042 --> 04:12.377
Let's go.

04:12.419 --> 04:15.213
[ Yodeling ]

04:15.255 --> 04:18.967
* I wanna ride Old Paint
going at a run *
[ Cheering ]

04:19.009 --> 04:22.637
* I wanna feel the wind
in my face *

04:22.679 --> 04:26.266
* Thousand miles
from all these city lights *

04:26.307 --> 04:28.852
* Goin' at a cowhand's pace *

04:28.893 --> 04:32.731
* I wanna pillow my head
near the sleepin' herd *

04:32.772 --> 04:35.734
* While the moon shines down
from above *

04:35.775 --> 04:39.571
* I wanna strum my guitar
and yodel-le-hee-hee *

04:39.612 --> 04:42.991
* That's the life that I love *

04:43.033 --> 04:44.993
[ Yodeling ]

04:45.035 --> 04:45.994
Yeah!

04:46.036 --> 04:46.995
Whoo!

04:47.037 --> 04:49.289
[ Yodeling ]

04:49.330 --> 04:50.331
Whoa!

04:50.373 --> 04:58.965
[ Yodeling ]

04:59.007 --> 05:00.342
Wow!

05:00.383 --> 05:04.471
[ Yodeling ]

05:04.512 --> 05:05.972
[ Laughs ]

05:06.014 --> 05:08.725
[ Cheers and applause ]
Yeah!

05:08.767 --> 05:10.727
**

05:10.769 --> 05:13.104
Got four!

05:13.146 --> 05:15.148
Four chairs!

05:15.190 --> 05:16.900
**

05:16.941 --> 05:17.901
Yes!

05:17.942 --> 05:18.985
That was so fun.

05:19.986 --> 05:21.988
Ruby, I told you!

05:22.030 --> 05:23.656
Oh, my goodness.

05:23.698 --> 05:25.575
What is your name,
and where are you from?

05:25.617 --> 05:27.035
My name is Ruby Leigh.

05:27.077 --> 05:28.578
I am 16 years old,
and I'm from Foley, Missouri.

05:28.620 --> 05:29.829
What?!
What?!

05:29.871 --> 05:32.248
Oh, my God!

05:32.290 --> 05:34.668
I've truly never heard anything
like what you just did.

05:34.709 --> 05:37.462
Thank you.
I loved how clear
and precise

05:37.504 --> 05:40.090
and piercing and beautiful
your tone was.

05:40.131 --> 05:43.009
And then when you started
doing the yodeling, it was like,

05:43.051 --> 05:46.179
"How is a human being able to do
the things that you're doing?"

05:46.221 --> 05:48.181
You can win "The Voice,"
honestly.
Yeah.

05:48.223 --> 05:49.516
Whoo.

05:49.557 --> 05:52.185
I would love to coach you
on Team Legend.

05:52.227 --> 05:53.687
Thank you.

05:53.728 --> 05:56.314
Gwen: That was just cool.
I yodel a lot.

05:56.356 --> 05:59.359
Like...* High on a hill
with a lonely goat *

05:59.401 --> 06:01.611
* Yodel-le-hee, yodel-le-hee,
yodel-le-hee-hoo *

06:01.653 --> 06:02.862
[ Cheers and applause ]

06:02.904 --> 06:04.322
But you're way better
than me.

06:04.364 --> 06:07.659
There's just something
so powerful about being 16,

06:07.701 --> 06:09.869
playing the guitar,
having a style,

06:09.911 --> 06:11.579
like with the way
that you're dressed.

06:11.621 --> 06:13.540
And I'm, like,
blown away by you,

06:13.581 --> 06:15.041
and I would love
to work with you.

06:15.083 --> 06:16.543
Thank you.

06:16.584 --> 06:19.379
Your energy is just insane.
[ Laughs ]

06:19.421 --> 06:20.547
You got four chairs
for a reason.

06:20.588 --> 06:22.173
Gwen: Yeah.

06:22.215 --> 06:24.092
Whether we felt like we had
a chance against Reba or not.

06:24.134 --> 06:27.554
[ Laughter ]
The control and power
that you've got at 16

06:27.595 --> 06:28.763
is just insane.

06:28.805 --> 06:30.348
You're really exciting,

06:30.390 --> 06:33.226
and I would obviously love you
to be on myteam.

06:33.268 --> 06:34.644
[ Imitates Southern accent ]
Know what I'm saying?

06:34.686 --> 06:37.605
Oh, my God.
Myteam.

06:37.647 --> 06:39.149
Oh, brother.
You like that?

06:39.190 --> 06:41.317
That was the worst Southern
accent I've ever heard.

06:41.359 --> 06:42.861
I don't know, Reba.

06:42.902 --> 06:44.112
In my life.

06:44.154 --> 06:45.447
No.
[ Laughter ]

06:45.488 --> 06:46.489
In your life?

06:46.531 --> 06:47.741
In my life.

06:47.782 --> 06:49.784
Well, that dog won't hunt
with me, Reba.

06:49.826 --> 06:52.037
Oh, my God.
[ Laughs ]

06:52.078 --> 06:55.790
Ruby, as young as you are,
being a fan of Patsy Montana --

06:55.832 --> 06:58.001
I'm a third generation
rodeo brat,

06:58.043 --> 07:02.088
so Patsy Montana,
a country-western singer,

07:02.130 --> 07:03.048
not just country.

07:03.089 --> 07:04.591
There is a difference.
Mm-hmm.

07:04.632 --> 07:06.926
I'm very flattered,
very proud of my heritage

07:06.968 --> 07:08.636
that you're singing
this song.

07:08.678 --> 07:10.430
Matter of fact,
my mama could yodel,

07:10.472 --> 07:12.015
and she taught me
how to yodel.

07:12.057 --> 07:13.224
Ooh, I want to hear!

07:13.266 --> 07:21.649
[ Yodeling ]

07:21.691 --> 07:25.111
[ Rhythmic clapping ]

07:25.153 --> 07:28.740
[ Yodeling ]

07:28.782 --> 07:29.699
Yeah!

07:29.741 --> 07:32.202
[ Cheers and applause ]

07:32.243 --> 07:34.662
[ Normal voice ]
I can't believe what's going on
in this audition.

07:34.704 --> 07:37.624
But I do believe
that it would be a great idea

07:37.665 --> 07:39.834
if we got
the audience's opinion.

07:39.876 --> 07:42.962
Alright, audience,
what do you think?

07:43.004 --> 07:44.381
What?!

07:44.422 --> 07:46.508
What is this nonsense?

07:46.549 --> 07:49.135
[ Cheering ]
What is happening here?

07:49.177 --> 07:50.637
We're being sabotaged.
[ Audience chanting "Reba!" ]

07:50.679 --> 07:52.639
They're cheating!
Cheater!

07:52.681 --> 07:55.684
[ Cheers and applause ]

07:55.725 --> 07:56.893
That's the team.

07:56.935 --> 07:58.561
I feel so sorry for us.

07:58.603 --> 07:59.979
Any of us would be lucky
to coach you.

08:00.021 --> 08:02.774
Please tell us, who do you pick
as your coach, Ruby?

08:02.816 --> 08:07.153
[ Audience shouting ]

08:07.195 --> 08:08.446
That was so good.

08:08.488 --> 08:10.156
That was funny,
wasn't it?

08:10.198 --> 08:11.783
Come on.

08:11.825 --> 08:14.536
This is so hard because
I listen to all of you guys.

08:14.577 --> 08:16.538
**

08:16.579 --> 08:18.248
I pick Reba.

08:18.289 --> 08:19.958
* That's the night that the
lights went out in Georgia *

08:20.000 --> 08:21.251
Whoo!

08:21.292 --> 08:22.961
You know, I didn't know
what I was looking for

08:23.003 --> 08:26.172
when I came on "The Voice"
because I'm new to this.

08:26.214 --> 08:29.009
All: Reba! Reba! Reba!

08:29.050 --> 08:31.845
Reba: When Ruby started
yodeling, I was like,

08:31.886 --> 08:34.973
"Holy crap.
I really want her on my team."

08:35.015 --> 08:36.850
Come on.
Let's go have a tater tot.

08:36.891 --> 08:39.477
Ruby could be a star
and have a huge following

08:39.519 --> 08:41.730
because she's not afraid to go

08:41.771 --> 08:44.441
kinda against the grain
of nowadays.

08:44.482 --> 08:45.692
I'm on fire.

08:45.734 --> 08:48.194
Team Reba is
off to a great start.

08:48.236 --> 08:50.655
It was meant to be.
Thank y'all so much.
Y'all were precious.

08:50.697 --> 08:52.657
Loved that.
Loved it.

08:52.699 --> 08:55.243
[ Laughter ]

08:55.285 --> 08:57.662
[ Cheers and applause ]

08:57.704 --> 09:02.751
[ Yodeling ]

09:02.792 --> 09:05.378
Reba is a major threat.

09:05.420 --> 09:07.797
Congratulations on winning
"The Voice," Reba,

09:07.839 --> 09:10.675
your first season.
[ Laughter ]

09:10.717 --> 09:12.677
Anytime I'm the underdog,
I'm gonna fight.

09:12.719 --> 09:14.095
If I like the artist,
I'm gonna fight.

09:14.137 --> 09:16.848
I'm just looking for something
that is unique

09:16.890 --> 09:19.517
and just makes me feel
and believe.

09:19.559 --> 09:23.730
John: I don't trust you guys
in your red hair and all that.

09:23.772 --> 09:26.316
Do I need to get you
a John Legend beard

09:26.358 --> 09:28.485
or something to wear?

09:28.526 --> 09:30.445
How much did
Reba pay you to do that?

09:30.487 --> 09:31.571
What the hell
just happened?

09:31.613 --> 09:33.073
Daly: Still to come...

09:33.114 --> 09:35.200
* Take it off now, girl,
take it off now, girl *

09:35.241 --> 09:36.826
Let me just take this off
so you can see

09:36.868 --> 09:38.411
beneath my beautiful.

09:38.453 --> 09:39.704
Oh, okay.

09:39.746 --> 09:41.748
Whoa.
Shelton,
she's at it again.

09:41.790 --> 09:43.083
[ Laughter ]

09:43.124 --> 09:44.751
What do you like
to sing?

09:44.793 --> 09:46.586
Ephraim: * When you walk
through the door *

09:46.628 --> 09:48.338
Oh, my new song,
"Nervous."

09:48.380 --> 09:49.589
* I still get... *

09:49.631 --> 09:50.715
Nervous.

09:50.757 --> 09:52.676
[ Laughs ]

09:59.474 --> 10:00.809
* This is "The Voice" *

10:00.850 --> 10:02.477
Daly: Welcome back
to the blind auditions.

10:02.519 --> 10:05.814
**

10:05.855 --> 10:07.232
Juliette:
My name is Juliette Ojeda.

10:07.273 --> 10:10.443
I'm 20 years old,
and I'm from Miami, Florida.

10:11.736 --> 10:14.781
Being from Miami is such a gift.

10:14.823 --> 10:16.449
It's beautiful,

10:16.491 --> 10:19.077
and we have Cuban pastries
on every corner,

10:19.119 --> 10:21.996
and I can go to the beach
whenever I want.

10:22.038 --> 10:25.375
I didn't think
I would ever be here.

10:25.417 --> 10:29.587
I went from singing
with a hairbrush in my bathroom,

10:29.629 --> 10:31.673
pretending to be
in front of an audience,

10:31.715 --> 10:33.842
to, like, this reality.

10:33.883 --> 10:36.261
My dad would play songs
on the radio,

10:36.302 --> 10:40.181
salsa songs and his favorite
mariachis and Hispanic artists.

10:40.223 --> 10:43.852
And then eventually,
I started learning by ear.

10:43.893 --> 10:46.229
My parents are
originally from Cuba.

10:46.271 --> 10:50.525
My mother was a doctor.
My dad was a pilot.

10:50.567 --> 10:52.527
Once my parents got here,

10:52.569 --> 10:54.988
my mom started working
at the airport, actually,

10:55.030 --> 10:57.407
and then she started
nursing school.

10:57.449 --> 11:00.410
My dad started working, like,
random construction jobs.

11:00.452 --> 11:04.247
And he's a handyman and doing
great, and I'm grateful.

11:04.289 --> 11:06.416
It was so difficult
to escape communism.

11:06.458 --> 11:08.668
My dad has told me
the stories he's gone through

11:08.710 --> 11:11.629
and, like, swimming through
rivers, crossing borders.

11:11.671 --> 11:13.173
It's scary.

11:13.214 --> 11:16.718
And so, the fact that my parents
left what they loved,

11:16.760 --> 11:18.845
and they sacrificed
their entire lives

11:18.887 --> 11:20.096
'cause if they were caught,

11:20.138 --> 11:22.140
then who knows
what would have happened.

11:22.182 --> 11:24.601
I'm the first person
in my family to be born here.

11:24.642 --> 11:26.519
My life has been so easy,

11:26.561 --> 11:29.397
and I-I don't ever want
to disappoint them.

11:29.439 --> 11:30.607
**

11:30.648 --> 11:33.818
[ Speaking Spanish ]

11:33.860 --> 11:37.238
[ Speaking Spanish ]

11:37.280 --> 11:38.948
To have
such supportive parents,

11:38.990 --> 11:42.369
it means that I-I can
blindly trust

11:42.410 --> 11:45.080
what I -- what I want to follow
and what I want to do,

11:45.121 --> 11:47.415
and that they'll support me,
no matter what.

11:47.457 --> 11:50.293
Man: Now, our next artist
is entering now.

11:50.335 --> 11:53.088
Juliette:
I'm excited to perform.

11:53.129 --> 11:56.466
I hope the coaches take away
that I can be unique

11:56.508 --> 11:59.803
and take two completely
different genres of music

11:59.844 --> 12:01.805
and make them my own.

12:01.846 --> 12:05.433
It'll shock them,
in a good way, I hope.

12:09.270 --> 12:10.897
**

12:10.939 --> 12:12.607
Oh.
Alright.

12:12.649 --> 12:15.902
* Ol vídalo*
That's pretty.

12:15.944 --> 12:20.907
* Me dicen todos*

12:20.949 --> 12:25.286
* El corazón me dice no*

12:25.328 --> 12:27.580
Ooh.

12:27.622 --> 12:30.959
* Jamás olvidaré*

12:31.001 --> 12:38.466
* La bella historia que viví*

12:38.508 --> 12:41.261
[ Cheers and applause ]

12:41.302 --> 12:47.767
* Hoy sigo enamorada de ti*

12:47.809 --> 12:50.520
* But now there's nowhere
to hide *

12:50.562 --> 12:52.981
* Since you pushed
my love aside *

12:53.023 --> 12:55.442
* I'm out of my head *

12:55.483 --> 13:00.321
* I'm hopelessly devoted
to you *

13:00.363 --> 13:07.328
* I'm hopelessly devoted to you,
babe *

13:07.370 --> 13:12.709
* Hopelessly devoted to you *

13:12.751 --> 13:14.336
Eh!

13:14.377 --> 13:17.005
* Hoy ya no puedo tener*
You like it?
I like that!

13:17.047 --> 13:19.674
* La felicidad de ayer*

13:19.716 --> 13:22.052
* Logré compartir*

13:22.093 --> 13:26.806
* Hoy sigo enamorada de ti*

13:26.848 --> 13:34.189
* I'm hopelessly devoted
to you *

13:34.230 --> 13:40.403
* Sigo enamorada de ti*

13:40.445 --> 13:41.654
Hey!

13:41.696 --> 13:43.198
Whoo!

13:43.239 --> 13:45.408
[ Cheers and applause ]

13:45.450 --> 13:48.912
**

13:48.953 --> 13:50.663
Niall: Energy.
Yeah.

13:50.705 --> 13:51.831
What is your name?

13:51.873 --> 13:53.375
I am Juliette Ojeda.

13:53.416 --> 13:55.377
Juliette,
congratulations.

13:55.418 --> 13:57.212
You're such
a dynamic artist.

13:57.253 --> 13:59.130
That was such
a fun performance.

13:59.172 --> 14:00.465
It was like
a roller coaster.

14:00.507 --> 14:02.926
It was like all these things
were happening.

14:02.967 --> 14:04.552
Good.
That's what I wanted.

14:04.594 --> 14:07.430
But it was exciting.
[ Laughs ]

14:07.472 --> 14:10.058
I would love to coach you
because I feel like

14:10.100 --> 14:12.310
I can teach you how to,
like, take control

14:12.352 --> 14:14.562
a little bit more
of the performance

14:14.604 --> 14:15.647
and when to let loose.

14:15.689 --> 14:18.566
And I just love your energy,
your spirit.

14:18.608 --> 14:20.860
I can see that
you're about ready to blossom,

14:20.902 --> 14:22.237
and I want to be there
for that.

14:22.278 --> 14:25.699
So, I would love for you
to be on Team Gwen.

14:25.740 --> 14:26.741
Hello, Juliette.

14:26.783 --> 14:28.576
Hi, Niall.
No!

14:28.618 --> 14:30.578
Oh.
Okay. Alright.

14:30.620 --> 14:32.330
I'm a Directioner.
I don't know.

14:32.372 --> 14:34.874
Totally over.
Don't fall for this.
Now, listen.

14:34.916 --> 14:36.126
That look
on her face.

14:36.167 --> 14:37.419
This is business, okay?

14:37.460 --> 14:39.087
I'm a girls' girl,
don't worry.

14:39.129 --> 14:41.131
This is the rest of your life.
Don't waste it.

14:41.172 --> 14:42.257
I honestly think
that Gwen thinks

14:42.298 --> 14:43.925
I have cooties
or something.

14:43.967 --> 14:45.969
I don't think
you have cooties.

14:46.011 --> 14:49.431
Juliette, that was crazy,
in a really good way.
Thank you.

14:49.472 --> 14:52.267
We don't really get too many
bilingual singers on here.

14:52.308 --> 14:54.936
Where did your singing
journey start?

14:54.978 --> 14:56.479
No one in my family
does this.

14:56.521 --> 14:58.481
I'm a first generation
Cuban American,

14:58.523 --> 15:01.651
and my parents
have sacrificed their lives

15:01.693 --> 15:03.236
to come to this country.

15:03.278 --> 15:05.071
It'd be kind of silly for me
to not follow my dreams.

15:05.113 --> 15:06.573
They followed theirs,
so why can't I?

15:06.614 --> 15:07.824
Yes.
I love that.

15:07.866 --> 15:09.075
Oh, my gosh.
So cute.

15:09.117 --> 15:12.287
You're cute as a button.
Thank you.

15:12.328 --> 15:15.123
I can't speak Spanish.
Very poquito.

15:15.165 --> 15:16.291
[ Laughter ]

15:16.332 --> 15:18.168
I can only speak
two languages,

15:18.209 --> 15:20.170
which is English,
good and bad.

15:20.211 --> 15:23.465
So, very impressed
with what you did.

15:23.506 --> 15:26.843
I think I could be
a really good coach for you,

15:26.885 --> 15:28.303
help you out
on a few things,

15:28.345 --> 15:31.514
stage performing,
communicating with the audience,

15:31.556 --> 15:33.975
and then you can teach me
how to speak Spanish.

15:34.017 --> 15:35.977
[ Laughter ]
Perfect.

15:36.019 --> 15:38.146
Let's get real here,
okay?

15:38.188 --> 15:40.315
100%, you have to pick me.

15:40.357 --> 15:42.817
If you don't pick me,
it's gonna be a huge mistake.

15:42.859 --> 15:45.403
And we're --
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa.

15:45.445 --> 15:47.113
I'm just gonna vote
for myself.

15:47.155 --> 15:48.156
Please pick me.

15:48.198 --> 15:49.783
[ Laughter ]

15:49.824 --> 15:52.285
Juliette, you need
to make a decision.

15:52.327 --> 15:54.662
Who do you pick
as your coach?

15:54.704 --> 15:55.955
Okay.

15:55.997 --> 15:58.667
[ Audience shouting ]

15:58.708 --> 16:08.176
**

16:08.218 --> 16:09.219
It's Gwen!

16:09.260 --> 16:11.680
I got picked?!
I got picked!

16:11.721 --> 16:12.972
Oh, my God!

16:13.014 --> 16:15.308
I am really excited
to get Juliette.

16:15.350 --> 16:17.352
She's really bringing
her own personality

16:17.394 --> 16:21.189
and her roots with her,
and she has that fire, you know.

16:21.231 --> 16:23.066
I fought so hard,
and it paid off.

16:23.108 --> 16:24.818
Way to go.
Well done, Gwennie.

16:24.859 --> 16:27.654
I'm glad I fought harder,
you know?
You did good.

16:27.696 --> 16:29.614
You wouldn't take no
for an answer.

16:36.913 --> 16:37.914
* This is "The Voice" *

16:37.956 --> 16:39.457
Daly: Welcome back.

16:41.126 --> 16:45.422
It is so great this season
to have the one and only Reba

16:45.463 --> 16:47.924
joining our coaching panel.
[ Cheers and applause ]

16:47.966 --> 16:50.176
Thank you very much.
Thank you.

16:50.218 --> 16:52.137
It's, um...

16:52.178 --> 16:54.431
Man: Oh, Reba! Reba!
I think --

16:54.472 --> 16:55.849
Daly: I'm sorry, sir.
Sir.

16:55.890 --> 16:59.227
Reba -- Sir.
Queen -- The Queen of Country!

16:59.269 --> 17:01.604
Hey,
is that Howie Mandel?

17:01.646 --> 17:02.564
Oh!

17:02.605 --> 17:05.025
Oh, my God.
Howie Mandel.

17:05.066 --> 17:06.109
What?

17:06.151 --> 17:07.193
Howie: Miss Reba!

17:07.235 --> 17:08.778
Howie,
what are you doing here?

17:08.820 --> 17:09.946
I love Reba!

17:09.988 --> 17:12.449
We're right next door
shooting "AGT" finale.

17:12.490 --> 17:14.909
Would you sign my shirt?
Reba: I would love to.

17:14.951 --> 17:16.161
[ Cheers and applause ]

17:16.202 --> 17:17.954
Howie Mandel,
ladies and gentlemen.

17:17.996 --> 17:20.331
Oh, my gosh.
Sign it
right on the heart.

17:20.373 --> 17:21.791
Right on the heart.
Right on the heart.

17:21.833 --> 17:23.376
Right on the heart.

17:23.418 --> 17:26.087
Whoo!
Would you be still?!

17:26.129 --> 17:28.298
No, I can't!
I love you!

17:28.340 --> 17:30.508
I love you.
Wow, a hug.

17:30.550 --> 17:31.968
You don't see
that every day.

17:32.010 --> 17:33.261
Reba!

17:33.303 --> 17:35.597
All: Reba! Reba! Reba!
What is happening?

17:35.638 --> 17:36.931
Reba! Reba!

17:36.973 --> 17:39.351
Daly: Howie Mandel!
Reba!

17:39.392 --> 17:41.853
Good luck on the "AGT" finale,
buddy.

17:41.895 --> 17:43.646
Wow, I don't even know
what just happened.

17:43.688 --> 17:45.148
What was that?
I was shocked!

17:45.190 --> 17:47.650
**

17:47.692 --> 17:49.361
Julia:
I remember when I was little,

17:49.402 --> 17:52.447
I used to sing "All of Me"
all the time.

17:52.489 --> 17:55.325
And Niall -- I always have
this weird thought.

17:55.367 --> 17:58.745
I have a feeling
he smells really good.

17:58.787 --> 18:01.081
I'm gonna be singing
for four superstars.

18:01.122 --> 18:03.041
Huh, it's crazy.
[ Laughs ]

18:03.083 --> 18:04.584
We're ready.

18:04.626 --> 18:06.670
I think the sound of my voice
is kind of unexpected

18:06.711 --> 18:08.254
because
I'm in eighth grade,

18:08.296 --> 18:12.217
and at 13, I'm the youngest
person in this competition.

18:12.258 --> 18:13.843
Here she comes.
Here she comes.
Oh, my God.
She looks so good.

18:13.885 --> 18:17.514
And I usually get,
like, the jaw drop.

18:17.555 --> 18:20.266
Well, hopefully
that's what I'll get.

18:21.393 --> 18:23.269
This is crazy.

18:24.312 --> 18:26.272
**

18:26.314 --> 18:32.112
* Stars shining bright
above you *

18:32.153 --> 18:37.075
* Night breezes seem
to whisper "I love you" *

18:37.117 --> 18:42.205
* Birds singing
in the sycamore tree *

18:42.247 --> 18:47.252
* Dream a little dream of me *

18:48.003 --> 18:51.881
* Say nighty-night and kiss me *
Get it!

18:51.923 --> 18:53.299
She did it!

18:53.341 --> 18:58.388
* Just hold me tight
and tell me you'll miss me *

18:58.430 --> 19:03.226
* While I'm alone
and blue as can be *

19:03.268 --> 19:07.814
* Dream a little dream of me *

19:07.856 --> 19:09.232
Her voice.

19:09.274 --> 19:11.067
* Stars fading *

19:11.109 --> 19:14.446
* But I linger on, dear *

19:14.487 --> 19:19.743
* Still craving your kiss *

19:19.784 --> 19:24.914
* I'm longing to linger
till dawn, dear *

19:24.956 --> 19:30.086
* I'm just saying this *

19:30.128 --> 19:35.508
* Sweet dreams that leave
all worries far behind you *

19:35.550 --> 19:40.263
* But in your dreams,
whatever they be *

19:40.305 --> 19:45.393
* Dream a little dream of me *

19:45.435 --> 19:48.605
* Dream a little dream of *

19:48.646 --> 19:50.357
Oh, my God.
Ooh!

19:50.398 --> 19:55.070
* Meeeeee *

19:55.111 --> 19:56.654
Wow.

19:57.447 --> 19:58.656
Oh, my God.
Aww.

19:58.698 --> 20:00.116
[ Cheers and applause ]

20:00.158 --> 20:02.369
Come on,
I'm dying to see.

20:02.410 --> 20:03.953
She's crying!

20:03.995 --> 20:05.121
**

20:05.163 --> 20:07.540
Hello. Hi.
Hi.

20:07.582 --> 20:09.292
Who are you?
I'm Julia Roome.

20:09.334 --> 20:12.253
I'm 13 years old,
and I live in Warwick, New York.
She's 13 years old!

20:12.295 --> 20:14.130
Niall: What?
13?!

20:14.172 --> 20:16.466
Oh, my gosh.
My little muffin.

20:16.508 --> 20:17.842
Can I have a hug?

20:17.884 --> 20:19.678
You did so good.

20:19.719 --> 20:20.804
Thank you so much.
You're doing so good.

20:20.845 --> 20:22.555
You can take a nice,
deep breath.

20:22.597 --> 20:23.890
You did so good.

20:23.932 --> 20:25.850
I couldn't even tie my shoelaces
at 13.

20:25.892 --> 20:26.810
[ Laughter ]

20:26.851 --> 20:28.561
And I still
haven't learned.

20:28.603 --> 20:29.979
That's a you problem,
Niall.

20:30.021 --> 20:31.690
The fact that you're 13
and you sing like that

20:31.731 --> 20:32.982
makes me want to vomit.

20:33.024 --> 20:33.900
Like, that is just --

20:33.942 --> 20:35.610
Oh, my God.
In a good way.

20:35.652 --> 20:36.820
In a good way.
Niall.

20:36.861 --> 20:38.822
I hope so.
[ Chuckles ]

20:38.863 --> 20:42.242
I have a bit of a thing
with girls with unique tones.

20:42.283 --> 20:43.743
Yes, I know, last season.

20:43.785 --> 20:44.953
I don't know if you watched
last season.

20:44.994 --> 20:46.037
I sure did.

20:46.079 --> 20:47.163
You're so cute.

20:47.205 --> 20:48.832
That's not fair.
It's very fair.

20:48.873 --> 20:50.458
You know what's not fair?
What?

20:50.500 --> 20:52.669
The cute Irish accent.

20:52.711 --> 20:55.088
Are you a One Direction fan,
Niall fan?

20:55.130 --> 20:57.382
I sure was.
[ Laughs ]

20:57.424 --> 20:59.342
Was?!
Am! Sorry. Sorry.

20:59.384 --> 21:01.177
I'm joking.
Oopsy!

21:01.219 --> 21:03.513
I had goose bumps from the
second you opened your mouth.

21:03.555 --> 21:06.099
It was very dreamy.
Kind of like Lana-esque.

21:06.141 --> 21:08.977
If I get the chance to work
with you, I'll be proud myself.

21:09.019 --> 21:10.311
Oh, thank you.

21:10.353 --> 21:11.312
Good luck, Gwen.

21:11.354 --> 21:12.689
[ Laughter ]

21:12.731 --> 21:14.024
Follow that one, huh?

21:14.065 --> 21:15.692
Wow.
He's so rude.

21:15.734 --> 21:17.360
You want to work with a rude boy
like that?

21:17.402 --> 21:19.487
Niall: I was cute five minutes
ago. What's going on?

21:19.529 --> 21:21.948
It reminded me of that
old-fashioned --

21:21.990 --> 21:24.826
like, I used to be
so into anything vintage.

21:24.868 --> 21:26.786
One of the first performances
I ever did,

21:26.828 --> 21:29.789
I was doing this, like, song,
and it really was like,

21:29.831 --> 21:33.668
* Sister, you've been
on my mind *

21:33.710 --> 21:37.881
* Sister,
we're two of a kind *

21:37.922 --> 21:39.632
* So *

21:39.674 --> 21:41.760
It felt kind of soulful
in the sense that

21:41.801 --> 21:45.096
it was coming from a true,
pure place inside your heart.

21:45.138 --> 21:47.474
And I'd love to work with you.
I think it'd be really fun.

21:47.515 --> 21:48.725
Thank you.

21:48.767 --> 21:51.561
I was like,
"Wow, this is a young person

21:51.603 --> 21:54.898
who has real,
like, fire and spark.

21:54.939 --> 21:57.692
I wasn't here when Niall won
with the younger artist.

21:57.734 --> 21:59.778
Having seen Gwen work
with younger artists,

21:59.819 --> 22:01.529
I know
that she'll help you

22:01.571 --> 22:03.156
do the things you need to do
to win the show.

22:03.198 --> 22:05.158
Wow.
He wasn't here
when I won.

22:05.200 --> 22:06.159
[ Laughter ]

22:06.201 --> 22:07.577
Wow. I owe you.

22:07.619 --> 22:10.413
Well, Julia,
congratulations on making it.

22:10.455 --> 22:12.082
And have fun.
Thank you.

22:12.123 --> 22:15.418
That is the A number-one piece
of advice I would give you...

22:15.460 --> 22:16.711
Yes.

22:16.753 --> 22:18.046
...above all else.
Thank you so much.

22:18.088 --> 22:20.548
Julia, who do you pick
as your coach?

22:20.590 --> 22:22.842
[ Audience shouting ]

22:22.884 --> 22:27.555
**

22:27.597 --> 22:30.684
Okay, I'm going to go
with my gut

22:30.725 --> 22:32.435
and go with...

22:32.477 --> 22:34.604
I think...

22:34.646 --> 22:36.815
[ Laughs ]
I don't know.

22:36.856 --> 22:39.693
**

22:45.323 --> 22:47.075
* This is "The Voice" *

22:47.117 --> 22:48.910
Daly: Welcome back.

22:48.952 --> 22:51.454
Niall: Julia, who do you
pick as your coach?

22:51.496 --> 22:52.956
[ Audience shouting ]

22:52.997 --> 22:56.376
Okay, I'm going to go
with my gut

22:56.418 --> 22:58.670
and go with...

22:58.712 --> 23:00.005
I think...

23:00.046 --> 23:03.341
[ Laughs ]
I don't know.

23:03.383 --> 23:05.427
[ Exhales sharply ] I think
I'm gonna go with Niall.

23:05.468 --> 23:09.180
* Baby, you light up my world
like nobody else *

23:09.222 --> 23:12.017
First time going head to head
with Gwen Stefani for Julia.

23:12.058 --> 23:14.853
Thank you.
You are a little superstar.

23:14.894 --> 23:17.022
To sing in that tone
with that maturity,

23:17.063 --> 23:20.483
at her age of 13,
is unprecedented.

23:20.525 --> 23:21.776
I've never seen it before,

23:21.818 --> 23:23.653
and I cannot wait
to see what comes next.

23:23.695 --> 23:24.988
* If only you saw
what I can see *

23:25.030 --> 23:26.865
* You'll understand
why I want you *

23:26.906 --> 23:29.325
I'm shocked
by all the young talent.

23:29.367 --> 23:30.535
Oh!

23:30.577 --> 23:32.162
So many young kids
are coming out

23:32.203 --> 23:34.873
singing great songs,
great vocals.

23:34.914 --> 23:37.000
For us who have been
in the business for a while,

23:37.042 --> 23:37.876
it's comforting.

23:37.917 --> 23:39.419
This is our future.

23:39.461 --> 23:41.046
* That's what makes you
beautiful *
Hello.

23:41.087 --> 23:43.923
I picked Niall
because I saw how he worked

23:43.965 --> 23:46.051
with a younger age last season.

23:46.092 --> 23:48.762
And I just felt like
he was the best for me.

23:48.803 --> 23:51.681
* That's what makes you
beautiful *

23:51.723 --> 23:54.893
Team Niall is off
to a flier.

23:54.934 --> 23:58.063
[ Irish music plays ]

23:58.104 --> 23:59.981
Okay,
give it to us here.

24:00.023 --> 24:05.111
**

24:05.153 --> 24:06.321
[ Laughs ]

24:06.363 --> 24:07.697
Like that, Reba?
Very good.

24:07.739 --> 24:09.866
Is that real?
Like -- Like you know how --

24:09.908 --> 24:11.409
I haven't got a clue
what I'm doing.

24:11.451 --> 24:13.244
[ Laughter ]

24:13.286 --> 24:15.455
**

24:15.497 --> 24:16.790
My name is Ayvio.

24:16.831 --> 24:18.124
I live in Lawton, Oklahoma,

24:18.166 --> 24:21.002
and I am a long-term
substitute teacher.

24:21.044 --> 24:24.005
Now it's time for
"What Do You Know? Tic-Tac-Toe."

24:24.047 --> 24:27.008
The way I teach these kids,
it's like a game show.

24:27.050 --> 24:28.760
True or false,
during the Stone Age...

24:28.802 --> 24:31.721
I think my schoolkids
will be very excited

24:31.763 --> 24:33.098
to hear me sing
or see me up here,

24:33.139 --> 24:34.933
but I never would
tell them my age.

24:34.974 --> 24:37.435
So, I think they really
want to see how old I am.

24:37.477 --> 24:39.104
[ Laughs ]

24:39.145 --> 24:41.773
36. There you go, students.
You got it.

24:41.815 --> 24:46.111
I started doing music
for myself around 2019,

24:46.152 --> 24:49.239
but we have three sons
and a daughter,

24:49.280 --> 24:51.658
so these days I'm more
of a chauffeur than a musician.

24:51.700 --> 24:53.868
We are really excited.

24:53.910 --> 24:55.912
I-I don't know
if I speak for everyone.

24:55.954 --> 24:57.997
I think
they're extra excited.

24:58.039 --> 25:00.375
I have kids who dream big.

25:00.417 --> 25:01.876
I've been chasing this

25:01.918 --> 25:05.005
so they would have the courage
to do it themselves.

25:05.046 --> 25:08.425
**

25:08.466 --> 25:09.801
Oh, snap.
[ Laughs ]

25:09.843 --> 25:12.595
This is your moment.
We are extremely proud of you.

25:12.637 --> 25:14.639
Do your best.
Leave it out there.

25:14.681 --> 25:16.641
Alright.
Let's do this.

25:16.683 --> 25:19.352
**

25:19.394 --> 25:21.146
The stakes are high for me.

25:21.187 --> 25:23.523
Man: We're ready for you
on stage, Ayvio.
Oh, for real?

25:23.565 --> 25:27.235
This music could open up a new
way to take care of my family.

25:27.277 --> 25:29.946
This just means
everything to me to be here.

25:29.988 --> 25:32.115
[ Whispers ] Hi, guys.

25:32.157 --> 25:34.034
I'm gonna
watch with you.
Okay.

25:34.075 --> 25:35.493
How are you?
Good. How are you?

25:35.535 --> 25:37.162
It's nice to meet you.
Hi.
So nice to meet you.

25:37.203 --> 25:38.496
This is Carson Daly.

25:38.538 --> 25:40.707
Alright, let's get a chair.
Come on.
Okay.

25:41.624 --> 25:44.544
**

25:44.586 --> 25:46.338
[ Cheers and applause ]

25:46.379 --> 25:48.631
* I see you driving
'round town *

25:48.673 --> 25:50.133
* With the girl I love *

25:50.175 --> 25:53.511
* And I'm like, forget you *

25:53.553 --> 25:57.849
* I guess the change
in my pocket wasn't enough *

25:57.891 --> 26:00.185
* I'm like, forget you *

26:00.226 --> 26:01.603
Come on, John.
I see your arm.

26:01.644 --> 26:03.063
* Listen here, I'm sorry *

26:03.104 --> 26:05.523
* I can't afford a Ferrari *

26:05.565 --> 26:08.526
* But that don't mean
I can't get you there *

26:08.568 --> 26:13.031
* I guess he's an Xbox
and I'm more of an Atari *

26:13.073 --> 26:15.617
* But the way you play
your game ain't fair *

26:15.658 --> 26:20.997
* I pity the fool
that falls in love with you *

26:21.039 --> 26:22.874
* Oops, she's a gold digger *

26:22.916 --> 26:24.292
* I just thought
