to have you on Team Niall.

39:24.406 --> 39:26.408
Seriously.
[ Applause ]

39:26.449 --> 39:28.034
Thank you.
Thank you.

39:28.785 --> 39:29.744
Are you done?

39:29.786 --> 39:31.496
[ Laughter ]

39:31.538 --> 39:32.580
Yes, ma'am.

39:32.622 --> 39:33.748
He said,
"Yes, ma'am."

39:33.790 --> 39:35.166
Yes, Mama Reba.

39:35.208 --> 39:36.584
When I found out

39:36.626 --> 39:37.961
who the coaches
were gonna be this year,

39:38.003 --> 39:40.422
my wife screamed
at the top of her lungs --

39:40.463 --> 39:41.423
When she heard my name.

39:41.464 --> 39:43.550
...and said, "Reba!"

39:43.591 --> 39:45.260
[ Laughter ]

39:45.301 --> 39:47.095
It's an honor to get
to hear you sing.

39:47.137 --> 39:49.848
Boy,
you are a firecracker.

39:49.889 --> 39:51.099
You were explosive.

39:51.141 --> 39:54.561
You were dynamic
all over the stage.

39:54.602 --> 39:55.937
Thank you
for the kind words,

39:55.979 --> 39:57.897
and I would love
to have you on Team Reba.

39:57.939 --> 39:59.274
We'd have a blast.

39:59.315 --> 40:03.194
I loved that performance.
He called it angst.

40:03.236 --> 40:04.821
I like to call it
urgency.

40:04.863 --> 40:07.198
And you were singing it
like your life depended on it,

40:07.240 --> 40:09.117
which is a powerful thing
to witness.

40:09.159 --> 40:11.953
It's very, like, mesmerizing
as an audience member.

40:11.995 --> 40:14.122
And not only did you
give us that feeling,

40:14.164 --> 40:17.667
but you were executing the song
with great skill

40:17.709 --> 40:19.794
as a vocalist, too,
at the same time.

40:19.836 --> 40:21.713
So,
congratulations on that.

40:21.755 --> 40:25.300
One of my inspirations
is you, sir.

40:25.342 --> 40:27.177
Oh. Thank you.

40:27.218 --> 40:29.054
My daughter sings
with me sometimes, too.

40:29.095 --> 40:30.930
Do you want
to bring her out?

40:30.972 --> 40:32.265
Evie.
You get to go sing.

40:32.307 --> 40:34.142
[ Laughs ]

40:35.852 --> 40:37.520
John: Oh, my God.
Look at her.

40:37.562 --> 40:39.147
Gwen: Oh, my God.

40:39.189 --> 40:41.858
[ Laughs ]

40:41.900 --> 40:43.318
What's your daughter's
name?

40:43.360 --> 40:45.278
Evelyn Ann Owens.

40:45.320 --> 40:47.781
What do you like to sing,
Miss Evelyn Ann Owens?

40:47.822 --> 40:50.116
* When you walk
through the door *

40:50.158 --> 40:51.618
Oh, my new song,
"Nervous."

40:51.659 --> 40:54.120
* And you look
in my eyes *

40:54.162 --> 40:56.122
* Yeah, it feels,
yeah, it feels *

40:56.164 --> 40:58.166
* Like the very
first time *

40:58.208 --> 41:03.838
* I can fall for you forever,
I'm certain *

41:03.880 --> 41:06.383
* But I still get... *

41:06.424 --> 41:07.717
Nervous.

41:07.759 --> 41:09.344
[ Laughter ]

41:09.386 --> 41:13.014
I'm dead. [ Laughs ]

41:13.056 --> 41:15.892
That song is my daughter's
favorite song, too.

41:15.934 --> 41:17.394
And whoever gets
the honor to coach you

41:17.435 --> 41:19.020
will have so much fun
working with you.

41:19.062 --> 41:21.606
So, who do you pick
as your coach, Ephraim?

41:21.648 --> 41:24.734
[ Audience shouting ]

41:24.776 --> 41:27.028
Come on, Ephraim!
Come on, Ephraim!

41:27.070 --> 41:28.822
I have a varsity jacket
for you.

41:28.863 --> 41:30.407
Right here!
Right here!

41:30.448 --> 41:32.367
**

41:32.409 --> 41:34.661
Who should I pick?

41:34.703 --> 41:37.205
Look at my little dress!

41:37.247 --> 41:38.206
Come on, Evelyn.

41:38.248 --> 41:40.166
John,
I'm with you, dawg.

41:40.208 --> 41:42.794
[ Cheers and applause ]
[ Laughs ]

41:42.836 --> 41:44.713
John: Ephraim --
he sounded so beautiful

41:44.754 --> 41:46.047
in the low part of the song.

41:46.089 --> 41:49.551
Rich baritone,
but then had that raspy quality.

41:49.592 --> 41:51.094
I wanted to meet Mom,
too.

41:51.136 --> 41:53.221
So, I'm curious to see
what else Ephraim's gonna do.

41:53.263 --> 41:54.431
That was cute.

41:54.472 --> 41:55.890
Yes!

41:55.932 --> 41:58.226
* No, no, no, no, no, no *

41:58.268 --> 42:00.437
I'm still
the four-chair king, baby!

42:00.478 --> 42:10.405
**

